First, we can easily tell thereâs no diamond that costs $1500â¦ odd. Perhaps itâs an even price that companies avoid?

Price Cut by Histograms

The different colors are: Fair, Good, Very Good, Premium, Ideal (in order of worst to best) Letâs plot it

p + geom_histogram(binwidth = 250, fill = "#6e9396") +

These graphs quickly show how most of the diamonds have either a premium or ideal cut have the highest frequency of all diamonds. The $1500 blank spot also sticks out.

A Closer Look

Letâs go through some of the different factors to see we can understand why an IF and VVS1 have the lowest median costs.

Looking at the box plot, diamonds of color G have the highest median as youâre paying top dollar for an IF D rock.

Letâs also look at the previous plot to see how carat plays a role.
